300 2429 95 (Title:) 95 SB
600 2429 740 (Argument order for copy\(\) is incorrect..) 740 SB
300 2478 145 (Section:) 145 SB
600 2478 508 (21.1.1.4.19 [lib.string::copy]) 508 SB
300 2527 125 (Status:) 125 SB
600 2527 110 (active) 110 SB
300 2576 228 (Description:) 228 SB
600 2625 699 (In private email, John Dlugosz wrote:) 699 SB
600 2674 1393 (\223In copy\(\) the arguments are in a different order than on other functions.  I) 1393 SB
600 2723 1428 (suppose this was to provide for a default on pos.  However, if someone does) 1428 SB
600 2772 1447 (specify both he will be likely to get them backwards and the compiler will not) 1447 SB
600 2821 1474 (catch this.  I feel it is a point of usability that is not worth the default argument.) 1474 SB
600 2870 684 (Provide two forms of copy\(\) instead:) 684 SB
1 #C
statusdict begin /manualfeed false store end
EJ RS
