600 1250 699 (In private email, John Dlugosz wrote:) 699 SB
600 1299 1452 (\223Also, totally unspecified, is the treatment of the `reserve' area with respect to) 1452 SB
600 1348 1446 (element creation and destruction.  I chose to construct elements in the reserve) 1446 SB
600 1397 1295 (area right away, and then the string grows into the reserve area using) 1295 SB
600 1446 1485 (assignment semantics.  This causes dramatic simplification in several areas, and) 1485 SB
600 1495 1362 (allows me to implement it without the need for in-place construction and) 1362 SB
600 1544 1422 (explicit destructor calls \(important when targeting cfront-based compilers\).\224) 1422 SB
